WEBVTT

00:03.586 --> 00:05.797
[rock music]

00:05.880 --> 00:08.299
(kids)
Pig!

00:09.426 --> 00:12.345
Goat!

00:13.555 --> 00:14.848
Banana!

00:14.931 --> 00:19.519
♪ ♪

00:19.602 --> 00:20.770
Cricket!

00:20.854 --> 00:28.153
♪ ♪

00:33.533 --> 00:35.160
A-a-a-achoo!

00:35.243 --> 00:38.413
(all)
Pig! Goat! Banana! Cricket!

00:42.041 --> 00:44.961
[eerie music]

00:45.044 --> 00:50.717
♪ ♪

00:53.052 --> 00:55.013
Happy Chalawunga, everybody!

00:55.096 --> 00:57.474
{\an3}(all)
Happy Chalawunga!

00:57.557 --> 01:00.143
Time to decorate
the tree house.

01:00.226 --> 01:02.520
[upbeat music]

01:02.604 --> 01:03.563
{\an3}[squeaks]

01:03.646 --> 01:05.022
♪ ♪

01:05.105 --> 01:07.358
{\an1}Can I press the button?
Can--can I press the button?

01:07.442 --> 01:09.819
{\an1}Please let me do it.
It's all I want to do!

01:09.903 --> 01:11.613
Well, all right.

01:11.696 --> 01:12.989
{\an1}Whoo!

01:13.072 --> 01:14.741
[blender whirring]

01:14.824 --> 01:20.830
♪ ♪

01:20.914 --> 01:22.415
[chewing]

01:24.083 --> 01:27.253
{\an5}(all)
Pig Goat Banana Cricket
Happy Chalawunga high-five!

01:27.337 --> 01:29.172
Okay, now that we got
that out of the way,

01:29.255 --> 01:31.216
{\an3}it's time to
give me presents.

01:31.299 --> 01:35.678
You mean, it's time for all
of us to exchange presents.

01:35.762 --> 01:37.847
{\an3}Yeah, uh, right.
Of course, exchange.

01:37.931 --> 01:38.932
(both)
This is for you.

01:39.015 --> 01:41.142
- Hey, hey!
- Those are for you.

01:41.226 --> 01:42.560
- This is for you.
- These are for you.

01:42.644 --> 01:43.812
- Hey!
- Don't open till I tell ya.

01:43.895 --> 01:44.896
Hey, thanks.

01:44.979 --> 01:47.190
(all)
Happy Chalawunga!

01:47.273 --> 01:47.607
{\an3}[chuckles]

01:47.690 --> 01:49.567
Hmm.

01:49.651 --> 01:51.194
Seems like someone
received presents,

01:51.277 --> 01:52.612
but didn't give any.

01:52.695 --> 01:54.364
Any thoughts on that, Banana?

01:54.447 --> 01:56.616
Uh, I...I wanted to get
you guys presents,

01:56.699 --> 01:58.409
but didn't make it
to the store.

01:58.493 --> 01:59.702
But--but you guys did,

01:59.786 --> 02:01.830
and that's what
Chalawunga's all about.

02:01.913 --> 02:05.208
Getting <i> me</i> stuff, right?

02:05.291 --> 02:08.044
No give-y presents,
no get-y presents.

02:08.127 --> 02:10.547
I'll just put 'em here
for safe keeping.

02:10.630 --> 02:14.092
Hey--oh, oh!
[struggles]

02:14.175 --> 02:15.510
Oh!

02:18.179 --> 02:22.225
{\an3}Once you give us presents,
you'll get these back.

02:22.308 --> 02:23.893
[bawling]

02:23.977 --> 02:25.144
He's crying.

02:25.228 --> 02:28.189
{\an1}Maybe we should
give him his presents anyway.

02:28.273 --> 02:30.066
Wait a second.

02:30.149 --> 02:31.234
Those aren't real!

02:31.317 --> 02:32.527
Those are Pocket Tears.

02:32.610 --> 02:34.946
Aah!

02:35.029 --> 02:37.991
[playful music]

02:38.074 --> 02:40.618
♪ ♪

02:40.702 --> 02:42.036
♪ Pocket Tears
Pocket Tears ♪

02:42.120 --> 02:44.581
♪ It always works
'cause it's Pocket Tears ♪

02:44.664 --> 02:46.165
[tears laughing]

02:46.249 --> 02:48.459
- ♪ Pocket Tears ♪
- Waah!

02:48.543 --> 02:50.545
(commercial announcer)
Pocket Tears may cause itching,

02:50.628 --> 02:51.838
rash, bloating,
or face diarrhea.

02:51.921 --> 02:53.423
[tears laughing]

02:53.506 --> 02:55.049
I'm getting my money back.

02:55.133 --> 02:57.135
[yawns]
I gotta get to sleep!

02:57.218 --> 02:59.888
Filthy the Foot
will be here any minute.

03:02.015 --> 03:04.100
{\an1}Oh, don't tell me
Pig still believes in

03:04.183 --> 03:05.268
Filthy the Foot.

03:05.351 --> 03:06.895
{\an8}I'll break it
to him gently.

03:06.978 --> 03:08.813
{\an8}Hey, Chowder Head,
get your butt over here.

03:08.897 --> 03:09.772
{\an8}I got some bad news.

03:09.856 --> 03:12.191
Are you crazy?

03:12.275 --> 03:13.818
We can't tell him
there's no Filthy the Foot.

03:13.902 --> 03:15.945
It will destroy him!

03:16.029 --> 03:17.572
Everything okay, guys?

03:17.655 --> 03:19.782
{\an9}Sure...we were talking about
how there's no such thing as--

03:19.866 --> 03:22.118
Filthy the Foot.

03:22.201 --> 03:23.578
What?
[laughs]

03:23.661 --> 03:26.122
You silly little
cuckoo doo-doo brains.

03:26.205 --> 03:27.624
Of course there is.

03:27.707 --> 03:29.626
It's all here
in Filthy's memoir,

03:29.709 --> 03:31.711
<i>One Heart, Five Toes.</i>

03:33.755 --> 03:35.298
Every Chalawunga,

03:35.381 --> 03:39.385
Filthy flies his sneaker sled
through the skies,

03:39.469 --> 03:42.639
then he gently places
the sparkle eggs

03:42.722 --> 03:45.558
on the lips of good boys
and girls everywhere.

03:45.642 --> 03:47.310
{\an3}[giggles]

03:47.393 --> 03:48.811
{\an1}And when you see
my sparkle egg

03:48.895 --> 03:52.190
{\an1}tomorrow morning, you'll know
that Filthy is real.

03:52.273 --> 03:53.566
Good night!

03:55.318 --> 03:58.363
♪ Yo ho ho, Filthy's coming
Filthy's coming ♪

03:58.446 --> 04:03.326
♪ Filthy the Foot
is coming to my lips ♪

04:05.995 --> 04:08.831
Filthy, I'm ready!

04:08.915 --> 04:10.917
[owl hoots]

04:11.000 --> 04:12.460
[rooster crows]

04:15.171 --> 04:16.547
No egg?

04:16.630 --> 04:20.134
Oh, sparkle egg, come out,
come out wherever you are.

04:20.218 --> 04:21.511
You must be here somewhere.

04:21.594 --> 04:22.512
{\an1}No egg?

04:22.595 --> 04:22.971
No egg?

04:23.054 --> 04:23.721
{\an3}No egg?

04:23.805 --> 04:25.598
[screams]

04:25.682 --> 04:26.808
[cries]

04:26.891 --> 04:28.476
What's up, Pig?

04:28.559 --> 04:31.437
{\an3}Flying Cat,
Filthy didn't come.

04:31.521 --> 04:32.188
Maybe he was busy.

04:32.271 --> 04:35.441
{\an3}Or completely
made up.

04:35.525 --> 04:38.319
{\an5}[sighs]
Or maybe I'll never know
what happened.

04:38.403 --> 04:39.112
{\an1}You could
just ask him.

04:39.195 --> 04:42.532
Ask him?
That's it!

04:42.615 --> 04:47.120
Flying Cat, you are so super
not dumb.

04:47.203 --> 04:48.079
[explosion]

04:48.162 --> 04:49.455
(Flying Cat)
Me-ouch!

04:49.539 --> 04:54.752
It says here that Filthy
lives in a secret lair

04:54.836 --> 04:57.213
in the deepest, darkest part
of the sewer.

04:57.296 --> 04:59.882
So, that's where I'm going!

04:59.966 --> 05:01.801
[uplifting music]

05:01.884 --> 05:07.223
I just follow Hairball Alley
to Yesterday's Tacos Boulevard

05:07.306 --> 05:10.518
and I'll be at Filthy's lair
in a jiff.

05:12.353 --> 05:13.563
Uh-oh.
Whoa.

05:13.646 --> 05:17.191
Whoa...

05:17.275 --> 05:18.234
Ugh!

05:18.317 --> 05:19.736
[blabbers]

05:19.819 --> 05:21.070
Aah!

05:21.154 --> 05:22.739
[snarls]

05:22.822 --> 05:24.532
Whew!
There's nothing about alligators

05:24.615 --> 05:26.409
on the--whoa!

05:26.492 --> 05:28.745
(Pig)
My book!

05:28.828 --> 05:31.414
Oh, no, I'll never find
Filthy now.

05:31.497 --> 05:33.708
- [roars]
- Aah!

05:33.791 --> 05:35.543
Filthy!
Where are you?

05:35.626 --> 05:39.338
{\an5}[cries]
Maybe Banana and Goat
were right.

05:39.422 --> 05:41.466
Maybe there is no
Filthy the Foot.

05:41.549 --> 05:43.926
Maybe I should just give up.

05:44.010 --> 05:47.513
[mysterious music]

05:47.597 --> 05:48.806
[man humming]

05:48.890 --> 05:52.185
[gasps]
It can't be.

05:52.268 --> 05:57.106
{\an3}[humming]

05:57.190 --> 06:01.444
- Filthy's theme song!
- [humming]

06:01.527 --> 06:04.614
[lively music]

06:04.697 --> 06:05.865
[bell jingles]

06:05.948 --> 06:08.326
[door whirring]

06:08.409 --> 06:09.410
[gasps]

06:09.494 --> 06:12.330
♪ ♪

06:12.413 --> 06:13.539
{\an1}Excuse me.

06:17.085 --> 06:19.128
[magical music]

06:19.212 --> 06:21.130
He is real.

06:21.214 --> 06:24.258
Who dares enter my fortress
of filth?

06:24.342 --> 06:26.511
Mr. Foot, it's me, Pig.

06:26.594 --> 06:28.638
{\an1}I just wanted to know
why didn't you put

06:28.721 --> 06:30.598
{\an1}a sparkle egg
on my lips?

06:30.681 --> 06:33.935
Nothing personal.
Truth is, I couldn't do it.

06:34.018 --> 06:35.353
I got the footroids.

06:35.436 --> 06:36.896
[thumping]

06:36.979 --> 06:39.315
And they hurt like
a son of a gorilla.

06:39.398 --> 06:41.943
Is there something I can do
to help?

06:42.026 --> 06:43.152
Nah.

06:43.236 --> 06:44.445
Maybe there is something.

06:44.529 --> 06:45.988
You could deliver
the sparkle eggs for me.

06:46.072 --> 06:49.408
{\an1}Wow!
But how can I?

06:49.492 --> 06:51.828
I'm just one,
unmagical pig.

06:51.911 --> 06:54.413
Not after I loan you some magic,
you won't be.

06:54.497 --> 06:56.040
[squeals]

06:57.083 --> 07:00.253
{\an3}Now kneel.

07:00.336 --> 07:03.840
{\an3}Do you solemnly swear
to deliver sparkle eggs

07:03.923 --> 07:06.467
to every single living
creature on the planet

07:06.551 --> 07:08.761
in just a few short hours?

07:08.845 --> 07:10.555
{\an1}I do.

07:10.638 --> 07:13.015
[heroic music]

07:13.099 --> 07:16.394
{\an3}Then I now dub you
Filthy the Pig.

07:16.477 --> 07:18.437
{\an3}[wretches]

07:18.521 --> 07:22.441
Magic sparkle vomit?
That's my favorite.

07:22.525 --> 07:25.736
{\an3}All right, you're done.
Ready to make a sparkle egg?

07:25.820 --> 07:26.737
I don't know if I can.

07:26.821 --> 07:29.448
Use the force,
but not too much.

07:29.532 --> 07:32.827
Don't want to blow
a main brain vein, bro.

07:32.910 --> 07:34.495
{\an1}[winces]

07:34.579 --> 07:37.623
- [bubbles popping]
- [yells]

07:37.707 --> 07:39.834
{\an1}Whoo.
Yipee, I did it!

07:39.917 --> 07:42.920
{\an3}Now hurry, you've got
eggs to deliver, homes.

07:43.004 --> 07:45.006
[sniffing]

07:45.089 --> 07:47.425
Kinda squishy
and stinky in here.

07:47.508 --> 07:50.553
Hey, I work hard, I play hard.

07:50.636 --> 07:53.431
I won't let you down, Filthy.

07:53.514 --> 07:56.475
[heroic music]

07:56.559 --> 08:01.063
♪ ♪

08:03.608 --> 08:07.403
[snoring softly]

08:07.486 --> 08:10.323
Come on, sparkle vomit.
Work your magic.

08:10.406 --> 08:11.657
[winces]

08:13.159 --> 08:15.369
[magical shimmering]

08:15.453 --> 08:18.331
Thank you, Filthy.

08:18.414 --> 08:21.667
Ooh, a glass of milk
and some arch supports.

08:25.171 --> 08:26.589
[heroic music]

08:26.672 --> 08:30.343
One down and six billion to go!

08:30.426 --> 08:31.260
♪ ♪

08:31.344 --> 08:33.011
[explodes]

08:33.095 --> 08:34.679
(kid)
Happy Chalawunga.

08:37.183 --> 08:40.102
[spy music]

08:40.186 --> 08:46.442
♪ ♪

08:46.525 --> 08:47.944
[beeping]

08:48.027 --> 08:49.195
♪ ♪

08:49.278 --> 08:50.780
[electricity sparking]
- Aah!

08:50.863 --> 08:52.198
Aah!
Ooh!

08:52.281 --> 08:53.658
Oh, nuts.

08:53.741 --> 08:57.995
- No give-y presents...
- No get-y presents.

08:58.079 --> 09:01.791
Yeah, yeah.
I'll get-y you presents.

09:03.209 --> 09:06.921
[mumbling]

09:07.004 --> 09:08.130
Okay, let's get this over with.

09:08.214 --> 09:10.091
[crowd clamoring]

09:10.174 --> 09:11.467
[back cracks]

09:11.550 --> 09:12.927
[all arguing over each other]

09:13.010 --> 09:14.762
Excuse me, out the way, move it.

09:17.265 --> 09:20.768
Ooh, the--
oh, these are great gifts.

09:20.851 --> 09:23.020
Oh, a rubber cockroach
for Cricket,

09:23.104 --> 09:24.689
a rubber cockroach
for Goat,

09:24.772 --> 09:27.608
and a rubber cockroach
for Pig--shopping done.

09:27.692 --> 09:30.945
I am such a wonderful
gift giver.

09:31.028 --> 09:32.154
[gasps]

09:32.238 --> 09:33.281
Oh.

09:33.364 --> 09:34.323
[shimmering]

09:34.407 --> 09:36.993
[magical music]

09:37.076 --> 09:39.036
Oh...

09:39.120 --> 09:42.373
Awesome shoes.

09:45.334 --> 09:48.004
[woman gasps and screams]

09:48.087 --> 09:49.797
(shoes)
I'm awesome.

09:49.880 --> 09:52.800
I'm awesome, I'm awesome,
I'm awesome, I'm awesome,

09:52.883 --> 09:54.760
I'm awesome, I'm awesome.

09:54.844 --> 09:57.680
These are the greatest sneakers
ever made.

09:57.763 --> 10:02.601
I don't need their crummy gifts.
I'll buy my own presents.

10:02.685 --> 10:04.020
What if these sneakers
get dirty?

10:04.103 --> 10:05.479
It'd be good to have
a backup pair,

10:05.563 --> 10:07.732
and a pair for fashion week,
and for the ping-pong tourney,

10:07.815 --> 10:11.360
and for--ooh,
Lincoln's birthday.

10:11.444 --> 10:13.529
[mumbling]

10:13.612 --> 10:16.657
And so no one else
can have any but me.

10:18.617 --> 10:19.243
Not so fast.

10:19.327 --> 10:22.246
Only one per customer.

10:22.330 --> 10:24.040
Store policy!

10:24.123 --> 10:26.500
- But--but--
- But nothing.

10:26.584 --> 10:27.084
Put 'em back!

10:27.168 --> 10:29.378
[inhales]

10:29.462 --> 10:31.672
Sure.
[chuckles]

10:31.756 --> 10:33.924
I'll put 'em back.

10:36.427 --> 10:38.846
[grunting]

10:38.929 --> 10:40.556
Hey, I like your style.

10:40.639 --> 10:43.476
- Oh!
- Hey, thanks.

10:43.559 --> 10:45.394
{\an3}Hello.

10:45.478 --> 10:46.645
{\an3}Hello.

10:46.729 --> 10:48.397
{\an3}Hello!

10:48.481 --> 10:49.065
{\an3}Hello.

10:49.148 --> 10:52.026
{\an3}Hello.

10:53.486 --> 10:56.781
[laughs]
Come to Daddy.

10:56.864 --> 10:57.740
[menacing music]

10:57.823 --> 10:59.742
{\an3}Huh?
[shrieks]

10:59.825 --> 11:05.039
{\an1}I am the ghost
of Chalawunga future.

11:05.122 --> 11:07.041
{\an3}If you want my sneakers,
the answer is no.

11:07.124 --> 11:09.377
Really?

11:09.460 --> 11:13.297
Were you not here to
buy presents for your friends?

11:13.381 --> 11:15.883
{\an3}This is what awaits you
if you keep up

11:15.966 --> 11:18.761
this selfish behavior.

11:18.844 --> 11:20.096
Oh!

11:22.598 --> 11:27.103
This will be your future
unless you change your ways.

11:27.186 --> 11:29.563
{\an3}[meows]

11:29.647 --> 11:32.775
Um--uh--sure, I'm...
I'm old and alone in a cemetery

11:32.858 --> 11:36.028
with nothing
but my awesome shoes?

11:36.112 --> 11:38.364
{\an3}Exactly.

11:38.447 --> 11:41.200
- Yeah, I'm okay with that.
- Wait, what?

11:45.746 --> 11:48.290
{\an5}(shoes)
I'm awesome, I'm awesome,
I'm awesome, I'm--

11:48.374 --> 11:49.333
[stammers]

11:49.417 --> 11:51.460
{\an3}Hey, it's only one
per customer!

11:51.544 --> 11:53.295
He's breaking story policy.

11:53.379 --> 11:55.339
[alarm sounds]

11:55.423 --> 11:58.717
{\an1}Uh...

11:58.801 --> 12:00.177
Aah-oh!

12:01.554 --> 12:05.266
{\an1}You never break
store policy.

12:05.349 --> 12:08.185
{\an3}That stupid stereotypical
ghost is a liar.

12:08.269 --> 12:11.313
He said I would end up
alone in a graveyard,

12:11.397 --> 12:12.773
but this is prison.

12:12.857 --> 12:14.775
This is way worse.

12:14.859 --> 12:16.152
{\an3}No shoes.

12:16.235 --> 12:17.486
{\an3}No friends.

12:17.570 --> 12:20.030
{\an3}[cries]

12:22.741 --> 12:24.118
♪ Prison Tears
Prison Tears ♪

12:27.413 --> 12:30.166
♪ Chalawunga boo-bunga ♪

12:30.249 --> 12:33.919
♪ Careful not to step
in dog doo dunga ♪

12:34.003 --> 12:37.006
♪ Me like to eat some
egg fu young-a ♪

12:37.089 --> 12:44.513
♪ On this holiday caa-a-a-alled
Chala-wunga ♪

12:44.597 --> 12:46.265
Ay!
So, what do you think?

12:46.348 --> 12:48.809
Bravo, delightfully catchy.

12:48.893 --> 12:51.520
{\an3}Thanks, I'm gonna sing
it at the Chalawunga parade

12:51.604 --> 12:53.856
and everyone's going to love it.

12:53.939 --> 12:55.399
They asked you?

12:55.483 --> 12:56.400
Technically, no.

12:56.484 --> 13:00.112
But then I asked me,
and I said yes!

13:00.196 --> 13:01.697
Pardon me, excuse me.

13:01.780 --> 13:04.325
[parade music]

13:04.408 --> 13:07.077
{\an5}(Goat)
VIG here.
Very Important Goat.

13:07.161 --> 13:08.037
[giggles]

13:08.120 --> 13:09.330
Excuse me, Ma'am.

13:09.413 --> 13:11.457
{\an1}What is the best way
to sneak into the parade?

13:11.540 --> 13:12.791
- What?
- What?

13:12.875 --> 13:14.335
{\an3}You want to get into
the parade,

13:14.418 --> 13:16.003
where's your badge?

13:20.424 --> 13:22.551
Oh, here you go.

13:22.635 --> 13:25.304
You just wrote parade
on a piece of cheese!

13:25.387 --> 13:26.305
[retches]

13:26.388 --> 13:28.599
[flies buzzing]

13:28.682 --> 13:30.059
[Goat panting]

13:30.142 --> 13:32.603
And now it is my pleasure
to introduce to you

13:32.686 --> 13:39.068
Broadway's latest singing
sensation, Lila Twinklepipes.

13:39.151 --> 13:40.903
[groans]

13:40.986 --> 13:41.946
{\an3}[laughs]

13:42.029 --> 13:42.947
[cheering]

13:43.030 --> 13:48.786
[groaning]

13:49.787 --> 13:51.038
Ha-ha!

13:51.121 --> 13:53.165
Being a celeb
on this fabulous float

13:53.249 --> 13:56.335
was a dream of mine,
a dream that came true.

13:56.418 --> 13:59.713
Odds are, your dreams won't.
It's just math, people.

13:59.797 --> 14:00.673
[crowd groans]

14:00.756 --> 14:02.299
That's messed up, son.

14:02.383 --> 14:05.177
But you keep dreaming anyway.

14:05.261 --> 14:06.595
(crowd)
Yay!

14:06.679 --> 14:10.808
This one's called
<i>Chalawunga Dreams.</i>

14:10.891 --> 14:12.268
[inhales]
Ugh!

14:12.351 --> 14:14.603
♪ Chalawunga boo-bunga ♪

14:14.687 --> 14:16.981
♪ Careful not to step
in dog doo-- ♪

14:17.064 --> 14:19.483
{\an1}Get lost!
No one wants to hear you sing.

14:19.567 --> 14:20.609
(all)
Boo!

14:20.693 --> 14:22.111
Stop hogging the limelight.

14:22.194 --> 14:24.029
{\an3}I've got Chalawunga dreams
of my own.

14:24.113 --> 14:25.114
{\an3}♪ Dunga ♪

14:25.197 --> 14:26.824
♪ Me like to eat-- ♪

14:26.907 --> 14:27.783
Give me--

14:27.866 --> 14:30.536
[overlapping arguing]

14:33.330 --> 14:34.456
Huh!

14:34.540 --> 14:35.791
[panting]

14:35.874 --> 14:38.794
[exciting music]

14:38.877 --> 14:40.796
[whimpering]

14:40.879 --> 14:43.465
Hee-yow!

14:43.549 --> 14:45.801
Whoa!

14:45.884 --> 14:48.804
[babbling]

14:48.887 --> 14:50.639
Argh!

14:50.723 --> 14:53.309
Whoa!

14:53.392 --> 14:54.893
[crowd gasping]

14:54.977 --> 14:56.520
This is my big chance.

14:56.604 --> 14:59.398
Happy Chalawunga, everybody!

14:59.481 --> 15:01.692
[cheering]

15:01.775 --> 15:04.612
♪ Chalawunga boo-bunga ♪

15:04.695 --> 15:08.282
♪ Careful not to step in
dog doo-dunga ♪

15:08.365 --> 15:11.493
{\an5}(all)
♪ Me like to eat some
egg fu young-a ♪

15:11.577 --> 15:16.040
♪ On this holiday
caa-a-a-alled ♪

15:16.123 --> 15:18.876
(all)
♪ Chalawunga ♪

15:18.959 --> 15:20.252
♪ Chalawunga boo-bunga ♪

15:20.336 --> 15:22.921
Get out of the way!
There's so many clouds.

15:23.005 --> 15:24.340
♪ Step in dog-- ♪

15:24.423 --> 15:25.716
{\an3}Hey!

15:25.799 --> 15:30.095
{\an3}♪ Don't fly your
sneaker into ♪

15:30.179 --> 15:32.556
My boo-bunga!

15:32.640 --> 15:34.350
{\an1}[wails]

15:34.433 --> 15:36.685
Aah!
Whoa!

15:36.769 --> 15:38.020
[groans]

15:38.979 --> 15:40.272
[menacing music]

15:40.356 --> 15:41.732
Mm.

15:41.815 --> 15:43.692
{\an1}[groans]

15:43.776 --> 15:46.403
{\an1}Hi, Goat.
Sorry I ruined your boo-bunga.

15:46.487 --> 15:49.531
They loved me, Pig.
They really, really loved me.

15:49.615 --> 15:51.325
I'm a sensation.

15:54.161 --> 15:58.374
[playing harmonica]

15:58.457 --> 16:03.962
{\an8}♪ I got those jailhouse
Chalawunga blues again ♪

16:04.046 --> 16:05.673
{\an8}Goat?
Pig?

16:05.756 --> 16:06.882
(both)
Hey, Banana.

16:06.965 --> 16:08.884
[somber harmonica notes]

16:08.967 --> 16:10.177
These are my homies.

16:10.260 --> 16:13.639
Earless Eddie
and Graveyard Gary.

16:14.973 --> 16:18.018
Who wants a sparkle egg?

16:18.102 --> 16:20.062
I can't hear you.

16:20.145 --> 16:21.480
[shimmering]

16:21.563 --> 16:24.233
[magical music]

16:25.651 --> 16:28.445
{\an3}Burgerstein, who does Pig
love more than anyone?

16:28.529 --> 16:29.530
[gibberish]

16:29.613 --> 16:30.864
{\an3}Right!
Filthy the Foot.

16:30.948 --> 16:32.366
And who doesn't exist?

16:32.449 --> 16:33.450
[gibberish]

16:33.534 --> 16:35.077
Right, Filthy the Foot.

16:35.160 --> 16:39.039
{\an3}And who is the number one best
friend in the entire world?

16:39.123 --> 16:39.998
{\an1}[grunts]

16:40.082 --> 16:42.751
{\an3}What? No, wrong.
I-I am.

16:42.835 --> 16:45.087
You cut me deeply.

16:45.170 --> 16:49.007
Presenting, Mecha Foot.

16:49.091 --> 16:50.843
[gasps]
And suddenly,

16:50.926 --> 16:54.763
the imaginary becomes reality!

16:54.847 --> 16:56.181
Aah.

16:56.265 --> 16:57.808
[beeps]

16:57.891 --> 17:01.103
Now, Mecha, remember
what I taught you to say.

17:01.186 --> 17:01.979
[whimpers]

17:02.062 --> 17:05.065
Happy Chalawunga, dudes.

17:05.148 --> 17:08.152
{\an1}[coughs]
Oh, that's wonderful.

17:08.234 --> 17:10.570
And now for the ultimate test.

17:10.654 --> 17:13.866
Make me a sparkle egg!

17:13.949 --> 17:14.825
[beeps]

17:14.907 --> 17:16.952
[puckering]

17:20.329 --> 17:24.001
Perfect.
Ooh, Pig is gonna be so happy.

17:24.084 --> 17:26.002
Wait, where are you going?

17:26.086 --> 17:28.047
{\an3}Mecha, listen to
your mommy.

17:28.130 --> 17:30.924
{\an3}Stop right there.
You're growing.

17:31.008 --> 17:34.470
{\an3}This is not supposed
to happen.

17:34.553 --> 17:35.888
Ah, no.

17:35.971 --> 17:39.808
I messed up Pig's
Chalawunga surprise.

17:39.892 --> 17:43.228
[roars]

17:43.312 --> 17:44.646
[screams]

17:44.730 --> 17:46.607
[roars]

17:46.690 --> 17:49.651
[lively music]

17:49.735 --> 17:53.739
♪ ♪

17:57.159 --> 17:58.076
[beeping]

17:58.160 --> 17:59.077
{\an1}(all)
Cricket!

17:59.161 --> 18:00.662
You guys okay?

18:00.746 --> 18:02.664
What's with the Godzilla foot?

18:02.748 --> 18:04.249
I made him for you, Pig.

18:04.333 --> 18:05.959
{\an1}You created
a horrible monster

18:06.043 --> 18:09.171
{\an1}who's trying to
destroy the city for me?

18:09.254 --> 18:11.256
Well, technically,
I guess I did.

18:11.340 --> 18:13.425
I didn't want you to be upset
when you found out

18:13.509 --> 18:16.053
Filthy wasn't real, so I...

18:16.136 --> 18:17.846
But Filthy <i> is</i> real.

18:17.930 --> 18:19.973
(all)
No, he's not!

18:20.057 --> 18:22.142
Well then, who's that?

18:22.226 --> 18:25.187
[heroic music]

18:25.270 --> 18:26.522
♪ ♪

18:26.605 --> 18:30.192
This Mecha Foot is giving
my holiday a bad name.

18:30.275 --> 18:31.902
Sweet Mama's monkey!

18:31.985 --> 18:33.946
I-I can't believe
what I'm seeing.

18:34.029 --> 18:36.281
{\an1}There really is
a Filthy the Foot.

18:36.365 --> 18:38.575
{\an3}I'm sorry we didn't
believe you, Pig.

18:38.659 --> 18:41.703
{\an3}You were right
and we were wrong.

18:41.787 --> 18:44.915
{\an5}(all)
Pig Goat Banana Cricket
apology accepted high-five!

18:44.998 --> 18:49.294
Hey, you big scrappy.
You metal meat head.

18:49.378 --> 18:52.756
[roars]

18:52.840 --> 18:54.216
(all)
Hmm.

18:54.299 --> 18:57.219
[lively music]

18:57.302 --> 19:01.765
♪ ♪

19:01.849 --> 19:05.894
You don't deserve to
wear the beard!

19:05.978 --> 19:07.604
Aah--ooh!

19:07.688 --> 19:08.897
[grunting]

19:08.981 --> 19:10.774
Filthy's footroids.

19:10.858 --> 19:13.151
(Pig)
They're slowing him down!

19:13.235 --> 19:19.700
♪ ♪

19:19.783 --> 19:22.953
Ah, sweet relief.

19:23.036 --> 19:26.707
[heroic music]

19:26.790 --> 19:28.500
Arch support!

19:28.584 --> 19:30.919
Achilles heel.

19:31.003 --> 19:32.754
- Hang nail attack.
- [roars]

19:32.838 --> 19:36.216
{\an5}(Filthy)
Needle piggies went
to your face.

19:36.300 --> 19:40.554
♪ ♪

19:40.637 --> 19:43.515
- Yay, Filthy, you did it!
- Great job. Ooh, yeah.

19:43.599 --> 19:45.267
{\an3}Oh, no!

19:45.350 --> 19:46.810
[menacing music]

19:46.894 --> 19:48.937
[roars]

19:49.021 --> 19:51.940
[groaning]

19:52.024 --> 19:57.195
♪ ♪

19:57.279 --> 19:59.823
[roars]

19:59.907 --> 20:03.076
[yells]

20:03.160 --> 20:05.746
{\an1}Filthy still
needs our help.

20:05.829 --> 20:07.873
Leave it to me.
I'll take care of this.

20:07.956 --> 20:12.044
Hey, Mecha, here's something
I learned to make in prison.

20:12.127 --> 20:15.797
- What is that?
- A toilet paper bazooka.

20:18.383 --> 20:20.135
(Banana)
Oh, well, I tried.

20:20.218 --> 20:21.595
[groans]

20:21.678 --> 20:24.932
(female mechanical voice)
Egg deposit in ten, nine...

20:25.015 --> 20:27.434
I got an idea.
Fly that-a way.

20:27.517 --> 20:30.479
[lively music]

20:30.562 --> 20:31.813
♪ ♪

20:31.897 --> 20:35.317
(female mechanical voice)
Seven, six, five...

20:35.400 --> 20:38.195
Four, three, two...

20:38.278 --> 20:39.488
[gasps]

20:39.571 --> 20:42.282
{\an5}(female mechanical voice)
Warning.
System--

20:42.366 --> 20:43.367
[explosion]

20:43.450 --> 20:45.327
[all cheering]

20:45.410 --> 20:47.996
- We did it!
- Well actually, I kinda did it.

20:48.080 --> 20:50.540
- I helped.
- Well, now, we all did.

20:50.624 --> 20:51.583
{\an1}Yeah.

20:51.667 --> 20:53.335
But mostly, I did.

20:58.966 --> 21:01.927
Filthy, sorry I didn't give
everyone on the planet

21:02.010 --> 21:03.053
a sparkle egg.

21:03.136 --> 21:05.847
{\an3}Hey, you delivered
more than I was gonna.

21:05.931 --> 21:07.557
[grunts]

21:09.434 --> 21:10.811
(Pig)
This is for you.

21:10.894 --> 21:12.312
Me?

21:12.396 --> 21:14.523
I've given out sparkle eggs
my whole life,

21:14.606 --> 21:16.566
but I never got one
in return.

21:16.650 --> 21:18.235
Thanks, Pig.

21:18.318 --> 21:20.112
[slurps]

21:20.195 --> 21:21.697
Let's bite it together.

21:21.780 --> 21:24.825
{\an5}[gasps]
It would be an honor
and a privilege.

21:24.908 --> 21:26.326
[poignant music]

21:26.410 --> 21:27.327
[crunch]

21:27.411 --> 21:29.204
♪ ♪

21:29.288 --> 21:30.664
[grunts]

21:30.747 --> 21:32.708
Ah!

21:32.791 --> 21:34.668
Happy Chalawunga.

21:34.751 --> 21:36.003
Indeed.

21:36.086 --> 21:38.839
And look who has gifts
for everyone!

21:38.922 --> 21:40.382
(all)
Thanks, Banana!

21:40.465 --> 21:42.634
Thanks, me.

21:42.718 --> 21:46.722
♪ ♪

21:46.805 --> 21:49.099
And these are for you.

21:49.182 --> 21:50.058
{\an3}[gasps]

21:50.142 --> 21:51.852
Rubber cockroaches?

21:51.935 --> 21:54.563
Aw, you guys.

21:54.646 --> 21:56.732
(all)
Happy Chalawunga!

21:56.815 --> 22:00.110
{\an5}(shoe)
Awesome, awesome,
awesome, awesome.

22:02.320 --> 22:05.240
[gentle guitar music]

22:05.323 --> 22:12.372
♪ ♪

22:25.635 --> 22:27.679
[balloon whistles]
